Class DefaultQueue

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.amelia.looper.queue.AbstractQueue
      • io.amelia.looper.queue.DefaultQueue

  • public class DefaultQueue
extends AbstractQueue
    Low-level class holding the list of entries and sometimes tasks.

    You can retrieve the looper for the current thread with LooperFactory.obtain() You can retrieve the queue for the looper from AbstractLooper.getQueue()

      • postBarrier

        public EntryBarrier postBarrier()
        Adds a barrier to this queue.

        Message processing occurs as usual until the message queue encounters the barrier that has been posted. When the barrier is encountered, later synchronous messages in the queue are stalled (prevented from being executed) until the barrier is released by calling cancelBarrier(long) and specifying the token that identifies the synchronization barrier.

        This method is used to immediately postpone execution of all subsequently posted synchronous messages until a condition is met that releases the barrier. Asynchronous messages (see EntryAbstract.isAsync() are exempt from the barrier and continue to be processed as usual.

        This call must be always matched by a call to cancelBarrier(long) with the same token to ensure that the message queue resumes normal operation. Otherwise the application will probably hang!

        Returns:
        The instance of the EntryBarrier which can be used to cancel the barrier.

      • postCheckpoint

        public EntryCheckpoint postCheckpoint(java.util.function.BiPredicate<AbstractLooper,java.lang.Boolean> predicate)
        Adds a checkpoint to this queue.

        The checkpoint is removed automatically for you by returning false from the BiPredicate.test(Object, Object) when it is invoked, or explicitly removing it with cancel(long).

        Parameters:
        predicate - The Predicate that is tested if the checkpoint should be removed from the queue. Predicate will be provided an instance of Looper and if there are more enqueued tasks that follow the checkpoint.
        Returns:
        The instance of QueueTask for easy tracking.
